A POLITICIAN is urging local organisations to nominate young people for the Money for Life Challenge. Learn skills with Money for Life A POLITICIAN is urging local organisations to nominate young people for the Money for Life Challenge.Cumbernauld and Kilsyth MSP Jamie Hepburn is promoting the competition which teaches 16-24-year-olds money management skills.He said: &quot;This is a great opportunity for young people to enhance their financial education.&quot;l www.moneyfor lifechallenge.org.uk 